pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> 2hs     mithral 2 hander 21/40 but with build in haste so delay is lower 30s I believe  -500pp or so<br><br>2hb     Ketcha Koro Miss (sp)   7/30  drops in Kunark - cheap<br><br>Friedrick 49th Warrior<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utugurok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tugurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 7:45:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pantheon.yale.edu/~bdiebold/images/TugReal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> Have to say I just can't stand reading about level 18 warriors worrying about should they upgrade to cobalt or just improve already excellent weapons. I know twinkage is cool these days, but I still think it should be done quietly.<br><br>Of course, I'm maybe a little bitter since I didn't get my first piece of cobalt until I was level 52. <p><p><A href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76073><img border="0" src="http://members.glaznor.org/signature/tugurok.jpg"</A></p><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uhouek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Houek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 7:52:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> I agree, Tugurok.  How much of a difference could cobalt boots make on a level 18?  I'm sure any warrior twink is wearing full crafted, so no level 18 mob is going to be able to do much damage to them, another 10 AC or so isn't going to change anything.  <br><br>I have a pally that I twinked out and I thought I was a real bad ass.  I gave him almost full bronze, the rest was banded, and I gave him a BABS.   This guy's using some of the same weapons my main is and he's almost 30 levels lower than me.<br><br>My suggestion is just play the game.  Anything better than bronze armor, and blackened alloy longswords, is overkill.  I don't believe it will make a meaningful difference to you at all.  Just level. <p><p align ="center"><a href ="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=35031"><img border="0"src="http://www.ryanbuck.com/images/houeknewban.gif" alt="Click here to see my Magelo profile!"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ueggrole1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eggrole1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 8:17:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> Sheesh guys, I did pay my dues as a noob untwinked mage so long ago. I played many alts with ok equipment, but for my war I decided to go all out for a change. Heck I even have a few toons on different servers so I have to play from scratch, and as much fun as that is I was just looking for something different to keep my interest up. Oh well, I guess i'll go with my gut and upgrade the armour...<br><br>-eggrole <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukorwynnnitewing.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Korwynn Nitewing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 8:36:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> At the lower levels, crafted is plenty sufficient to ensure that MOBS are going to have a hard time hitting you. That reduces the fighting down to YOUR damage output. Haste item first, prob FBSS unless you can afford better. Then get some seriously damaging weapons. My favorite for 1 hs up to about level 40 has to be the LSoEE, it just hits too hard to ignore.<br>If that is too pricey, any of the Centi weapons are a good combo until at least late 30's. After that, well you have to start worrying about keeping agro and such, so delay becomes more important. Hope that helps. <p><img src=http://members.home.net/dakar2/pics/korwynn.gif>Korwynn NitewingDruid of the 54th Circle of Tunare</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 304<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 4:42:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> Twinking is not a bad thing, but its pointless trying to maximize AC and weapons at this level. You won't see any difference in full crafted or full cobalt at this level since the mobs ATK that you are fighting is no where near the AC you will get from crafted or crusty.<br><br>If you want to put cobalt on a lvl 18, fine but you will not see a difference for many levels. <p><div align="center" style="font-size: 11px; font-family: arial"><img src="http://www.bfdesigns.net/eq/wandor_sig.jpg"><br><a target="_blank" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6103"><b>Wandor's profile</b></a> | <a target="_blank" href="http://www.exarch.net/"><b>Fusion of Flame</b></a> | <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6102" target="_blank"><b>Moordian's profile</b></a></div></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwandork.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wandor K</A> at: 2/9/02 1:41:18 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/utugurok.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tugurok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 8:36:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://pantheon.yale.edu/~bdiebold/images/TugReal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Weap or equip upgrade?</span><hr size=1> Well, if you *really* want to twink at that level, go for regen and haste, then weapons. Fungi (or even iksar) + good haste + nice weapons + halfway decent armor = mad exp at low levels. <p><p><A href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=76073><img border="0" src="http://members.glaznor.org/signature/tugurok.jpg"</A></p><br></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=1778.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=1778.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1778.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.emailToFriend?topicID=1778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.threadControl?topicID=1778.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1778.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=1778.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub14.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesteelwarriorthearena">The Arena<option value="thesteelwarriorthebattlefield">The BattleField<option value="thesteelwarriorthebunker">The Bunke